272
30:54.300 --> 30:57.840
The next example is superdense coding.

273
30:57.840 --> 31:06.960
Like quantum teleportation,
superdense coding is a protocol and what it accomplishes is complimentary to teleportation.

274
31:06.960 --> 31:13.520
Whereas teleportation allows
one qubit to be transmitted using an e-bit and two
classical bits of communication,

275
31:13.520 --> 31:21.180
superdense coding allows
two classical bits to be transmitted using
an e-bit and one qubit of quantum communication.

276
31:21.180 --> 31:28.860
So, in short, superdense coding allows for the transmission
of classical information and the reason it's
